<subSubSection id="C30A6528FFB3FF81C5BC1CD2FC4DFD83" pageId="17" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAF36A3FFB3FF81C5BC1CD2FC4DFD83" blockId="17.[174,1127,189,518]" pageId="17" pageNumber="52">
Taxonomic notes. This species was mentioned in the earlier publications as 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB3FF81C5981C8FFDC4FF7C" authority="(Bang-Haas, 1912)" baseAuthorityName="Bang-Haas" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[206,582,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mamestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspicua">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB3FF81C5981C8FFEDEFF7C" box="[206,348,224,249]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="52">P. conspicua</emphasis>
(Bang-Haas, 1912)
</taxonomicName>
. The synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB3FF81C6181C8FFC5CFF7C" authorityName="Eversmann" authorityYear="1856" box="[846,990,224,249]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="52" phylum="Nemertea" rank="species" species="vesperugo">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB3FF81C6181C8FFC5CFF7C" box="[846,990,224,249]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="52">P. vesperugo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was stated and the 
<typeStatus id="54AB8801FFB3FF81C4431D6EFE04FE9E" box="[277,390,257,283]" pageId="17" pageNumber="52">lectotype</typeStatus>
was designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B52FFB3FF81C7D71D6EFCE8FE9E" author="VARGA, Z. &amp; RONKAY, G. &amp; RONKAY, L." box="[641,874,257,283]" pageId="17" pageNumber="52" pagination="133 - 160" refId="ref12050" refString="VARGA, Z., RONKAY, G. &amp; RONKAY, L. (2017): Revised taxonomic check list of the Eurasiatic species of the subtribe Poliina (Noctuidae, Noctuinae, Hadenini). - Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 64 (2): 133 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / dez. 64.21455" type="journal article" year="2017">
VARGA 
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB3FF81C78D1D6DFC96FE9E" box="[731,788,257,283]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="52">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
. The geographically separated population groups of the species were originally described as distinct species (Sayan Mts: 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB3FF81C4B11D2AFCCDFEDB" authority="Bang-Haas, 1912" authorityName="Bang-Haas" authorityYear="1912" box="[487,847,324,350]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mamestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspicua">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB3FF81C4B11D2AFDF4FEDB" box="[487,630,325,350]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="52">P. conspicua</emphasis>
Bang-Haas, 1912
</taxonomicName>
; Russian Far East, Primorye distr.: 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB3FF81C40E1D09FD3BFEFA" authority="Sukhareva, 1976" authorityName="Sukhareva" authorityYear="1976" box="[344,697,357,383]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="52" phylum="Nemertea" rank="species" species="vasjurini">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB3FF81C40E1D09FE62FEFA" box="[344,480,358,383]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="52">P. vasjurini</emphasis>
Sukhareva, 1976
</taxonomicName>
; North 
<collectingCountry id="F3077633FFB3FF81C64D1D0AFCFFFEFA" box="[795,893,357,383]" name="Finland" pageId="17" pageNumber="52">Finland</collectingCountry>
, Inari: 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB3FF81C6811D09FEE3FE24" authority="Mikkola, 1980" authorityName="Mikkola" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="52" phylum="Nemertea" rank="species" species="sabmeana">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB3FF81C6811D09FBE4FEFA" box="[983,1126,357,383]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="52">P. sabmeana</emphasis>
Mikkola, 1980
</taxonomicName>
). They were considered as subspecies of a Siberian tundro-alpine species by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B52FFB3FF81C43A1DC6FDD8FE46" author="HACKER, H. &amp; RONKAY, L. &amp; HREBLAY, M." box="[364,602,425,451]" pageId="17" pageNumber="52" refId="ref10942" refString="HACKER, H., RONKAY, L. &amp; HREBLAY, M. (2002): Hadeninae I. In: FIBIGER, M. (ed.): Noctuidae Europaeae, vol. 4. - Entomological Press, Soro, 456 pp." type="book" year="2002">
HACKER 
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB3FF81C4841DC5FD8AFE46" box="[466,520,425,451]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="52">et al.</emphasis>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
, based on the presumably much larger distribution of the species (
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B52FFB3FF81C48D1DA5FD37FE61" author="KONONENKO, V. S." box="[475,693,458,484]" pageId="17" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref11161" refString="KONONENKO, V. S. (1990): Synonymic check list of the Noctuidae of the Primorye Territory, the Far East of U. S. S. R. - Tinea 13 (Suppl.): 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1990">KONONENKO 1990</bibRefCitation>
). However, the taxonomic analysis of these externally different populations requires further studies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
